  "text": "HTTP connection manager route matching in Envoy is implemented across several key C++ files and classes. The routing process consists of three main components: virtual host selection, route matching algorithm, and route action dispatch.\n\n**Virtual Host Selection:** The RouteMatcher class (source/common/router/config_impl.h and .cc) is the entry point for routing. The findVirtualHost() method (line 2113 in config_impl.cc) matches incoming requests to virtual hosts by:\n1. First performing an exact match on the lowercased host header against the virtual_hosts_ hashmap\n2. If no exact match, attempting suffix matching via findWildcardVirtualHost() for wildcard_virtual_host_suffixes_\n3. If no suffix match, attempting prefix matching for wildcard_virtual_host_prefixes_\n4. Falling back to the default_virtual_host_ if no matches are found\n\nThe CommonVirtualHostImpl and VirtualHostImpl classes (source/common/router/config_impl.h and .cc) represent virtual host configurations and hold all shared data for routes within a virtual host.\n\n**Route Matching Algorithm:** Once a virtual host is selected, the VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromEntries() method (line 1978 in config_impl.cc) performs the actual route matching. This method:\n1. Checks SSL redirect requirements\n2. Evaluates a matcher tree (if configured) using RouteMatchAction and RouteListMatchAction classes\n3. Calls getRouteFromRoutes() to iterate through candidate routes\n4. For each route, calls the matches() method on RouteEntryImplBase subclasses\n\nThe RouteEntryImplBase::matchRoute() method (line 669 in config_impl.h) performs common matching logic including header matching, metadata matching, TLS context matching, and runtime matching. Specific route types have their own matches() implementations:\n- PrefixRouteEntryImpl::matches() - prefix path matching\n- PathRouteEntryImpl::matches() - exact path matching\n- RegexRouteEntryImpl::matches() - regex path matching\n- ConnectRouteEntryImpl::matches() - CONNECT method matching\n- PathSeparatedPrefixRouteEntryImpl::matches() - path-separated prefix matching\n- UriTemplateMatcherRouteEntryImpl::matches() - URI template matching\n\n**Route Action Dispatch:** The router filter's Filter::decodeHeaders() method (line 431 in router.cc) calls callbacks_->route() which eventually calls the HTTP connection manager's route caching and refreshing logic. The ConnectionManagerImpl::ActiveStream::refreshCachedRoute() method (line 1608 in conn_manager_impl.cc) performs the actual route selection by calling snapped_route_config_->route().\n\nThe matching criteria for routes include metadata matching (MetadataMatchCriteriaImpl in metadatamatchcriteria_impl.h/cc) and TLS context matching (TlsContextMatchCriteriaImpl in tls_context_match_criteria_impl.h/cc)."
}

